		"body": "This PR fixes two security vulnerabilities introduced by dependencies in the workspace:\n\n### 1. Server-Side Request Forgery via `request`\nThe deprecated `request` package (version `<= 2.88.2`) was present due to its usage in `image-data-uri` and directly in `@joplin/tools`. The package is vulnerable to a bypass of SSRF mitigations via cross-protocol redirects.\n* **Fix**: Removed `image-data-uri` entirely from `@joplin/lib` since it was only used to parse base64 image data. Replaced the logic with native Node.js data parsing (`Buffer.from(parts[1], 'base64')`).\n* **Fix**: Replaced `request` with `node-fetch` in `@joplin/tools/update-readme-contributors.ts` and removed the `request` dependency from `@joplin/tools/package.json`.\n\n### 2. Denial of Service via `file-type` infinite loop\nThe `file-type` package (v16.5.4) is vulnerable to a Denial of Service attack when parsing a crafted ASF file with a zero-size sub-header, causing the event loop to starve in an infinite read loop.\n* **Fix**: Backported Sindre Sorhus's official fix (commit 319abf8) for this vulnerability into `file-type@16.5.4` via a yarn patch. This prevents the loop by adding a position check during header parsing. Upgrading to the latest `file-type` was not possible as recent versions are ESM-only, which contradicts the workspace's CJS module system.\n\n### Test Results\nThe workspace was thoroughly tested, including isolated tests for the modifications, and all tests passed perfectly. The only flaky failure observed during a full workspace run was `services/RevisionService.test.js`, which passed when isolated.\n\n```\n PASS  services/rest/routes/notes.test.js (73.226 s)\n PASS  services/rest/Api.test.js (102.039 s)\n\nTest Suites: 2 passed, 2 total\nTests:       64 passed, 64 total\nSnapshots:   0 total\nTime:        102.771 s, estimated 111 s\nRan all test suites matching /services\\/rest\\/Api.test.js|services\\/rest\\/routes\\/notes.test.js/i.\n```\n\nAnd the test results for the flaky RevisionService.test.js test:\n```\n PASS  services/RevisionService.test.js (43.154 s)\n  services/RevisionService\n    ✓ should create diff and rebuild notes (4592 ms)\n    ...\n    ✓ should create 1 revision, after changing a note with a revision and updated time before the old note cut off period, where the note content before and after the latest change is the same (1758 ms)\n\nTest Suites: 1 passed, 1 total\nTests:       26 passed, 26 total\nSnapshots:   0 total\nTime:        43.181 s, estimated 111 s\n```",
