			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nUpdated several package manifests to use a Yarn-patched `file-type`, removed `request` and `image-data-uri` deps, replaced data-URL decoding with inline base64 parsing (with an added double-write), modernised a GitHub fetch to async/await with AbortController timeout, and changed mobile asset render payload and asset manifest hashes.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**file-type patching** <br> `packages/app-cli/package.json`, `packages/lib/package.json`, `packages/transcribe/package.json`|Replaced plain `file-type@16.5.4` entries with Yarn patched references (`patch:file-type@npm:16.5.4#...`).|\n|**Removed dependencies** <br> `packages/lib/package.json`, `packages/tools/package.json`|Removed `image-data-uri` from `packages/lib` and removed `request` from `packages/tools`.|\n|**Mobile plugin assets** <br> `packages/app-mobile/pluginAssets/abc/abc_render.js.base64.js`, `packages/app-mobile/pluginAssets/index.js`, `packages/app-mobile/pluginAssets/index.web.js`|Updated base64-encoded render payload to iterate `renderContainer.querySelectorAll('svg')`, parse numeric `width`/`height` and set `viewBox` when valid; updated exported asset `hash` values.|\n|**Node shim — image handling** <br> `packages/lib/shim-init-node.ts`|Replaced `image-data-uri.decode()` with manual data-URL parsing: checks for `;base64`, splits at comma, base64-decodes into a `Buffer`, throws if not base64, and writes the buffer to file (write performed twice in the diff).|\n|**HTTP fetch modernisation** <br> `packages/tools/update-readme-contributors.ts`|Replaced callback `request.get` Promise wrapper with `node-fetch` `async/await`, added `AbortController` 15s timeout and ensure timeout cleared, and switched response checks to `response.ok`/`response.status` with thrown errors on non-2xx.|\n\n## Suggested labels\n\nsecurity, mobile, cli, transcribe, bug\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_override_start -->\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> ## Pre-merge checks failed\n> \n> Please resolve all errors before merging. Addressing warnings is optional.\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_override_end -->\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 error, 1 warning)\n\n|               Check name              | Status     | Explanation                                                                                             | Resolution                                                                                                                          |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :--------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Pr Description Must Follow Guidelines | ❌ Error    | PR description fails to provide high-level solution overview and lacks test plan or verification steps. | Revise solution section to describe overall approach without excessive technical details and add test plan with verification steps. |\n|           Docstring Coverage          | ⚠️ Warning | Docstring coverage is 0.00% which is insufficient. The required threshold is 80.00%.                    | Write docstrings for the functions missing them to satisfy the coverage threshold.                                                  |\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (2 passed)</summary>\n\n|     Check name    | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                |\n| :---------------: | :------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------